Marathon Starts Plant-Wide Turnaround at Canton Refinery

-- B y   A a r o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-02-28T17:47:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/marathon-starts-plant-wide-turnaround-at-canton-refinery-1-.html
  Marathon Oil Corp . has started
planned work at its Canton refinery in Ohio, according to a
company spokesman.  Shane Pochard, the spokesman, declined to comment on the
work’s duration or scope.  Marathon will perform a full plant turnaround at the Canton
refinery starting this month through April, Rob Knight, a public
health clerk for the Canton City Health Department’s Air
Pollution Control Division, said in an e-mail Feb. 24.  The refinery has a capacity of 84,500 barrels a day,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Aaron Clark  in New York at 
 aclark27@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at   dstets@bloomberg.net  